UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 75
1 AN ACT relating to local school board student representatives.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 160 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) Beginning with academic year 2026-2027, each local school board shall appoint
6 at least one (1) student representative to attend and participate in school board
7 meetings, provide student perspective on issues, and learn about school district
8 governance. The student representative shall not be a voting member but shall be
9 allowed to provide a nonbinding advisory vote on action items that is recorded in
10 the minutes of the meeting. The student representative shall not participate in
11 closed sessions of a school board meeting.
12 (2) A student representative shall:
13 (a) Be enrolled in a high school of the district or be a resident of the district
14 enrolled in a public high school contracted to provide high school service
15 pursuant to KRS 158.100(1);
16 (b) Be classified as a junior or senior at the time of appointment;
17 (c) Have completed the requirement of KRS 158.141; and
18 (d) Serve at least a one (1) year term.
19 (3) Each local school board shall adopt a policy to implement this section that
20 includes but is not limited to the student representative selection process,
21 eligibility requirements, and terms of service. The policy shall include the
22 following provisions:
23 (a) A student representative selection process that shall include an election by
24 high school students;
25 (b) An attendance requirement that allows a student representative to be absent
26 from a maximum of two (2) board meetings;
27 (c) Authorization for the student representative to use video teleconferencing in
